main event: Radar observation of multiple unidentified flying objects in the Mediterranean area on 26 December 1953.
interesting points: The radar showed stationary targets varying in shape and size from 10 to 15 feet in diameter., The radar observation lasted several minutes, with the targets appearing as blips at a range of 60-80 miles., Possible causes for the radar returns included anomalous propagation, submarines, or troops in flight., Observations conducted were by personnel of US-operated radar equipment., No photographs or physical evidence were recorded during the observations.
sighted object: multiple unidentified flying objects on radar
witness description: US military personnel operating radar equipment
